anuganj in the [[Balasore district]] in the state of Odisha, [[India]]. He graduated from the Januganj M. E. School in the year 1983 with an 'O\u2019 grade and stood 4th in Balasore Circle. He completed his [[matriculation]] from Remuna High School in [[Remuna]], [[Balasore]] in 1986. He was in the First division, securing a record mark (88%) in second language English in his H.S.C. Examination. He stood 3rd in [[Indian National Mathematical Olympiad|India National Mathematical Olympiad]] (Regional Level) Examination in 1987 while continuing with +2 Science at F. M. College, Balasore. He received his graduation degree from F. M. College, Balasore under [[Utkal University]] in the year 1991 in [[Physics]] with honours.\n\nJena was an MSc student in the P. G. Department of Physics at the [[Utkal University]] campus in [[Vani Vihar]], [[Bhubaneswar]] during the years 1991 through 1993. After successful completion of MSc in Physics with First class (Second position in Utkal University), he became a [[Research fellow|Junior Research Fellow]] in the [[National Institute for Interdisciplinary Science and Technology|Regional Research Laboratory]]Binhubaneswar. His proficiency as a meritorious student can be further evidenced from his success in qualifying IIT \u2013 GATE and CSIR \u2013 NET.\n\n==Profession==\nSri Jena, with keen interest in teaching, joined OES (Orissa Education Service) under the [[Department of Higher Education (India)|Department of Higher Education]], Orissa at the age of 28 years. He started his teaching career at the Department of Physics, Government College in [[Sundergarh|Sundargarh]], Orissa on 14 May 1999. He served for about 15 years at the Government College, Sundargarh and at the Government Women's Junior College in Sundargarh. Currently, he is working with the Department of Physics, Bhadrak Jr/Auto College in Bhadrak, Orissa (since 26 November 2013).\n\n==Writing career==\nSri Jena's contributions and achievements are of a superlative nature. it is said that his achievements and accomplishments in the dissemination of scientific culture and mindset are too many to enumerate.\n\nKamalakanta Jena, a distinguished [[academician]] in the field of Physics, is better known as a highly acclaimed writer of science articles and books throughout the state of Orissa and beyond. He started reporting in 1986 at the age of 15 years for 'The Chalachitra Jagat', one of the leading Cine Magazine published from [[Cuttack]]. His first article was published in the esteemed Oriya daily 'The Sambad' on 8 December 1991. His articles have been published in various magazines and journals, including The Sambad, The Prajatantra, [[The Samaja]], [[The Samaya]], The Dharitri, The Pragativadi, Bigyanaloka (Orissa Bigyan Prachar Samiti), Sansar, Meena Bazar, Nandan Kanan, Shisulekha, Sishu Prativa, Pourusha, Yojana, Akshay Urja, NBT Bulletin, Emerging Science, [[The Statesman (India)|The Statesman]], [[Science Reporter]] (NISCAIR) etc. Sri Jena, who is a Life Member of Orissa Bigyan Academy, is an eminent contributor to the flagship magazines of the Academy \u2013 \"Bigyan Academy\" and \"Science Horizon\". Despite his young age, he has more than 700 articles to his credit, published in almost all magazines and newspapers of repute in the state.\n\nSri Jena is a celebrated speaker on Popular Science in [[Talk radio|Radio Talk]] Programmes. His science talks aired in radio have been highly appreciated by the people. He worked as Editor of \"The South\", the annual magazine of South Hostel, F. M. College, Balasore, Orissa for the academic year 1990\u201391. He worked as Editor of The Vanisourav, the annual magazine of Godavarish Hostel, Utkal University Campus, Bhubaneswar for the academic year 1992\u201393. For the time being, he is working as Associate Editor, DIGBALAYA, Orissa Physical Society, Bhubaneswar. He represented Orissa Chapter as a prominent Science Communicator in the 99th [[Indian Science Congress Association|Indian Science Congress]] of 2012 held in [[KIIT University]], Bhubaneswar.\n\nNot only in Science, Sri Jena is also a noted humour writer. Many of his humour/satirical articles have been published in Haribol, Rabibara Samaja, Dharitri Chhutidina, Sambad, Byangabaani, Manorama, Tikie Hasa, Pragatibaadi, Lavanya, Teerataranga, Parichaya, Time Pass, Byanga Darabar etc. He is known as ADHAPOKA in the field of humours.\n\n==Books Written==\n\n'''[[Popular Science Books]]'''\n\n01. Kathaare Kathaare Bigyan (Pragati, Sundargarh),\n\n02. Barshaa Bijulira Khela (Vidyapuri, Cuttack),\n\n03. Chhota Nuhen Chhota Kathaa (Nalanda, Cuttack, selected by State Library),\n\n04. Big Bang Machine (The Book Point, Bhubaneswar),\n\n05. Gapare Gapare Bigyan (The Book Point, Bhubaneswar), Awarded by Orissa Bigyan Academy in 2011\n\n06. Barshaa Bijuli Ghadaghadi (Vidyapuri, Cuttack),\n\n07. Anapaaramparika Shakti (Holy Faith International, Cuttack),\n\n08. Gachha Lataara Gahana Kathaa (Holy Faith International, Cuttack)\n\n[[File:Popular Science 01.JPG|250px|Popular Science Books by Kamalakanta Jena]], [[File:Popular Science 02.JPG|250px|Popular Science Books by Kamalakanta Jena]]\n\n'''[[Text Books]]'''\n\n01. Environmental Education (+2, Vidyapuri, Cuttack),\n\n02. Paribesha Shiksha (+2, Vidyapuri, Cuttack),\n\n03. Practical Physics (+2, Nalanda, Cuttack),\n\n04. Ama Bigyan \u2013 Class I (Holy Faith International, Cuttack),\n\n05. Ama Bigyan \u2013 Class II (Holy Faith International, Cuttack),\n\n06. Ama Bigyan \u2013 Class III (Holy Faith International, Cuttack),\n\n07. Ama Bigyan \u2013 Class IV (Holy Faith International, Cuttack),\n\n08. Ama Bigyan \u2013 Class V (Holy Faith International, Cuttack)\n\n[[File:Text Book 01.JPG|250px|Text Books by Kamalakanta Jena]], [[File:Text Book 02.JPG|250px|Text Books by Kamalakanta Jena]]\n\n[[File:Paribesh Siksha.JPG|150px|College Text Book by Kamalakanta Jena on Environment, Publisher \u2013 Vidyapuri, Cuttack]], [[File:Environmental Education.JPG|150px|College Text Book by Kamalakanta Jena on Environment, Publisher \u2013 Vidyapuri, Cuttack]], [[File:Physics Practical XI.jpg|150px|Physics Practical Book by Kamalakanta Jena, Publisher \u2013 Nalanda, Cuttack]],\n[[File:Ama Bigyan 3.jpg|150px|Science Text Book for Class-III by Kamalakanta Jena, Publisher-Holy Faith International]], [[File:Ama Bigyan 4.jpg|150px|Science Text Book for Class-IV by Kamalakanta Jena, Publisher-Holy Faith International]], [[File:Ama Bigyan 5.jpg|150px|Science Text Book for Class-V by Kamalakanta Jena, Publisher-Holy Faith International]]\n\n* Barsa Bijulira Khela<ref>[http://www.vidyapuri.com/store/items/author/350 vidyapuri.com: KAMALAKANTA JENA]{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* Paribesa Sikhya\n* Solar cells grow thinner, but glow brighter<ref>[http://www.indiaenvironmentportal.org.in/category/author/kamalakanta-jena indiaenvironmentportal.org.in: Solar cells grow thinner, but glow brighter]</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nThe sincere commitment of Sri Jena to advancement of Science among common people in the state of Orissa and beyond has received recognitions from a multitude of academic and cultural institutions. His genuine efforts spreading awareness of environmental issues among the masses has been recognized by the award of the Prakruti Bandhu Puraskar by the Government of Orissa in the year 2007. He has been felicitated by various organisations including Bigyan Prachar Samiti, Orissa and awarded 'Prakruti Bandhu Puraskar' by Government of Orissa. Recently, he has been confirmed for '''Orissa Bigya Academy Award for the year 2011''' for his story book '''Gapare Gapare Bigyan''' on popular science.\n\nThe list of awards follows :\n\n# Award for Innovative Teaching Physics, 2012\t    : Kendriya Vidyalaya, Sundargarh\n# Pranakrushna Parija Popular Science Award, 2011   : Orissa Bigyan Academy, Bhubaneswar\n# Parashamanee Sammana, 2011                        : Parashamanee Magazine, Baripada\n# 